'''Koni De Winter''' (born 12 June 2002) is a Belgian<ref name="nieuwsblad.be">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20220315_97560464|title=Op bezoek bij Koni De Winter, de jongste basisspeler ooit bij Juventus in de Champions League: "Ik wil zoals Chiellini hier vijftien jaar spelen"|website=www.nieuwsblad.be |date=16 March 2022 }}</ref> professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for {{Italian football updater|Milan}} club [[AC Milan]] and the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]].

== Club career ==

=== Early career ===
De Winter played in City Pirates Antwerp until 2015.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=Attanasio|first=Christian|date=18 July 2020|title=Juve Primavera: Koni De Winter, il (primo) belga duttile arrivato a Torino|url=https://www.juventusnews24.com/juve-primavera-koni-de-winter-il-primo-belga-duttile-arrivato-a-torino-scheda/|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Juventus News 24|language=it-IT}}</ref> He played the 2015–16 season in the [[Lierse S.K. (1906)|Lierse SK]] youth academy.<ref name=":0" /> The following season, De Winter moved to the [[S.V. Zulte Waregem|Zulte Waregem]] youth academy.<ref name=":0" /> In the summer of 2018, he moved to Italian [[Serie A]] club [[Juventus FC|Juventus]], becoming the first Belgian footballer ever to play for them.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Koni De Winter: il jolly della Juve Under 17 che sogna di scrivere la storia|url=https://www.ilbianconero.com/a/koni-de-winter-il-jolly-della-juve-under-17-che-sogna-di-scriver-91481|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Juventus News - Ultime Notizie Juve - il BiancoNero|language=it}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{Cite web |title="Forse saranno della partita": chi sono De Winter, Soulé e Miretti, i giovani su cui punta Allegri |url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Juventus/10-09-2021/juventus-de-winter-soule-miretti-allegri-4201142538204.shtml |access-date=2022-03-06 |website=La Gazzetta dello Sport |date=10 September 2021 |language=it-IT}}</ref> Initially joining the [[Juventus FC Youth Sector|youth academy]], in the [[2018–19 Juventus FC season|2018–19 season]], De Winter made 27 appearances and scored one goal with the under-17s.<ref name=":1" /> In the [[2019–20 Juventus FC season|2019–20 season]], he made 8 appearances with the under-19s team.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Giocatore - KONI DE WINTER {{!}} Lega Serie A|url=http://www.legaseriea.it/it/giocatori/koni-de-winter/DWNRKN|access-date=2021-02-21|website=www.legaseriea.it|language=it}}</ref> The following season, De Winter made 23 appearances with the under-19s<ref>{{Cite web |title=Giocatore - KONI DE WINTER {{!}} Lega Serie A |url=https://www.legaseriea.it/it/giocatori/koni-de-winter/DWNRKN |access-date=2022-03-06 |website=www.legaseriea.it |language=it}}</ref> often playing as [[Captain (association football)|captain]].<ref name=":3" />

=== Juventus ===
==== First call-up by Juventus and 2021–22 season ====
On 28 October 2020, De Winter was called up by Juventus' first team coach [[Andrea Pirlo]] for a [[UEFA Champions League]] match against Spanish [[La Liga]] club [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=((Redazione JuventusNews24))|date=2020-10-28|title=Convocati Juve per il Barcellona: la decisione su Bonucci, 3 giovani in lista|url=https://www.juventusnews24.com/convocati-juve-barcellona-bonucci-de-winter-riccio-lista-pirlo/|access-date=2021-11-22|website=Juventus News 24|language=it-IT}}</ref> On 20 February 2021, he renewed his contract until 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-20|title=Juventus, il talento belga Koni De Winter ha rinnovato fino al 2024|url=https://it.blastingnews.com/calcio/2021/02/juventus-il-talento-belga-koni-de-winter-ha-rinnovato-fino-al-2024-003281340.html|access-date=2021-02-21|website=Blasting News|language=it}}</ref> On 24 July, he made his unofficial debut for Juventus in a 3–1 win against [[Cesena F.C.|Cesena]]; scoring the opening goal in the 4th minute.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|date=24 July 2021|title=Bianconeri win first preseason friendly! - Juventus|url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/articles/bianconeri-win-first-preseason-friendly|access-date=24 July 2021|website=|publisher=[[Juventus FC]]|language=en}}</ref>

De Winter made his debut for [[Juventus FC Under-23|Juventus U23]] – the reserve team of Juventus –  on 22 August 2021 in a 3–2 win against [[Pro Sesto 2013|Pro Sesto]] in the [[Coppa Italia Serie C]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Alessandro Villano |date=2021-08-22 |title=Pro Sesto Juventus U23 2-3 dts: i bianconeri avanzano in Coppa Italia |url=https://www.juventusnews24.com/pro-sesto-juventus-u23-sintesi-moviola-risultato-tabellino-cronaca-live-coppa-italia-serie-c-2021-22/ |access-date=2021-08-22 |website=Juventus News 24 |language=it-IT}}</ref> On 20 October, he was sent-off in a 2–2 draw against [[U.C. AlbinoLeffe|AlbinoLeffe]], ten minutes after his entry onto the field.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Baridon |first=Marco |date=2021-10-20 |title=Albinoleffe Juventus U23 2-2: Kaio Jorge e Pecorino per la doppia rimonta |url=https://www.juventusnews24.com/albinoleffe-juventus-u23-live-sintesi-moviola-risultato-tabellino-cronaca-serie-c-2021-22-highlights/ |access-date=2021-10-20 |website=Juventus News 24 |language=it-IT}}</ref> On 27 October, De Winter scored his first career goal: an equalizing goal in a 1–1 draw against [[Piacenza Calcio 1919|Piacenza]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Baridon |first=Marco |date=2021-10-27 |title=Piacenza Juventus U23 1-1: De Winter e i guanti di Garofani salvano Zauli |url=https://www.juventusnews24.com/piacenza-juventus-u23-live-sintesi-moviola-tabellino-risultato-cronaca-serie-c-2021-22-highlights/ |access-date=2021-10-27 |website=Juventus News 24 |language=it-IT}}</ref>

On 23 November, he made his official debut with the first team as well as his debut in the Champions League in a 4–0  defeat against English [[Premier League]] club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] coming on as substitute of [[Juan Cuadrado]] in the 81st minute.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Munno|first=Mauro|date=2021-11-23|title=Chelsea-Juve 4-0: tracollo bianconero a Stamford Bridge|url=https://www.juventusnews24.com/chelsea-juve-live-sintesi-moviola-risultato-tabellino-cronaca-highlights-champions-2021-22/|access-date=2021-11-23|website=Juventus News 24|language=it-IT}}</ref> On 8 December, De Winter made his debut as starter for the first team in a 1–0 win against [[Malmö FF]], becoming the youngest Juventus player to debut as a starter at {{Age in years and days|12 June 2002|8 December 2021|sep=and}};<ref>{{Cite web |author=((Redazione JuventusNews24))|date=2021-12-08 |title=De Winter da record: è il più giovane a riuscirci con la maglia della Juve |url=https://www.juventusnews24.com/de-winter-juve-record-giovane-titolare-champions-league-malmoe/ |access-date=2022-03-06 |website=Juventus News 24 |language=it-IT}}</ref> he was eventually susbstitued in the 70th minute by [[Mattia De Sciglio]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Munno|first=Mauro|date=2021-12-08|title=Juve Malmoe 1-0: Kean per il primato nel gruppo H|url=https://www.juventusnews24.com/juve-malmoe-live-sintesi-moviola-risultato-tabellino-cronaca-champions-league-2021-22-highlights/|access-date=2021-12-08|website=Juventus News 24|language=it-IT}}</ref>

On 29 January 2022, he had a [[Dislocated shoulder|luxation]] of his left [[shoulder]] during a match against [[Feralpisalò]].<ref>{{Cite web|author=((Redazione JuventusNews24))|date=2022-01-29|title=Infortunio De Winter: difensore ko in Juventus U23-Feralpisalò. Le condizioni|url=https://www.juventusnews24.com/infortunio-de-winter-juventus-u23-feralpisalo-ultime-notizie/|access-date=2022-01-29|website=Juventus News 24|language=it-IT}}</ref> On 6 March, De Winter returned from his injury in a 1–0 win against [[Pro Sesto 2013|Pro Sesto]] coming on as a substitute the 85th minute; four minutes later, De Winter scored the winning goal.<ref>{{Cite web |author=((Redazione JuventusNews24))|date=2022-03-06 |title=De Winter, rientro con gol: il belga subito decisivo per l'U23 |url=https://www.juventusnews24.com/juventus-u23-ritorno-campo-koni-de-winter-post-infortunio-gol/ |access-date=2022-03-06 |website=Juventus News 24 |language=it-IT}}</ref> After the end of the season, on 9 July, the defender officially renewed his contract with the club until 2026.<ref>{{Cite web |author=((Redazione JuventusNews24)) |date=2022-07-09 |title=De Winter rinnova con la Juventus: l'accordo è UFFICIALE – FOTO |url=https://www.juventusnews24.com/de-winter-rinnova-juventus-accordo-ufficiale/ |access-date=2022-07-09 |website=Juventus News 24 |language=it-IT}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{Cite web |date=2022-07-10 |title=Under 23, Koni De Winter in prestito all'Empoli |url=https://www.juventus.com/it/news/articoli/under-23-koni-de-winter-in-prestito-all-empoli |access-date=2022-07-10 |website=Juventus.com |language=it}}</ref>

==== Loan to Empoli ====
On 9 July 2022, the same day as his contract extension with Juventus was announced, De Winter was sent on loan to fellow [[Serie A]] side [[Empoli F.C.|Empoli]],<ref>{{Cite web |author=((Redazione JuventusNews24)) |date=2022-07-09 |title=De Winter Empoli, è UFFICIALE: depositato il contratto del difensore. I dettagli |url=https://www.juventusnews24.com/de-winter-empoli-ufficiale-contratto-lega-ultime-notizie-calciomercato/ |access-date=2022-07-10 |website=Juventus News 24 |language=it-IT}}</ref> with the deal being made official by both teams the following day.<ref name=":4" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-07-10 |title=Koni De Winter è un nuovo calciatore azzurro |url=https://empolifc.com/koni-de-winter-e-un-nuovo-calciatore-azzurro/ |access-date=2022-07-10 |website=Empoli FC |language=it-IT}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |author=((Redazione JuventusNews24)) |date=2022-07-10 |title=De Winter Empoli, il trasferimento ora è ufficiale: il comunicato della Juve |url=https://www.juventusnews24.com/de-winter-empoli-trasferimento-ufficiale-dettagli-prestito-secco-comunicato-juve/ |access-date=2022-07-10 |website=Juventus News 24 |language=it-IT}}</ref>

==== Loan to Genoa ====
On 11 August 2023, he moved on loan to [[Genoa CFC|Genoa]], with a conditional obligation to buy.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Genoa|url=https://genoacfc.it/2023/08/11/koni-de-winter-e-un-nuovo-giocatore-del-genoa/|title=KONI DE WINTER È UN GIOCATORE DEL GENOA|trans-title=KONI DE WINTER IS A GENOA PLAYER|date=11 August 2023|access-date=29 August 2023|language=it}}</ref>

=== Genoa ===
On 1 July 2024, De Winter was permanently transferred to Genoa ahead of the [[2024–25 Genoa CFC season|2024–25 season]], as the club achieved the conditional buy obligation for an estimated €8 million transfer fee.<ref>{{cite news |title=Koni De Winter è un giocatore del Genoa|url=https://genoacfc.it/2023/08/11/koni-de-winter-e-un-nuovo-giocatore-del-genoa/|access-date=11 August 2023 |publisher=Genoa CFC |date=11 August 2023 |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://football-italia.net/how-much-juventus-earn-from-de-winter-sale/|title=Official: How much Juventus earn from permanent defender's sale to Genoa|date=3 May 2024|website=Football Italia}}</ref>

=== AC Milan ===
On 13 August 2025, De Winter joined fellow Serie A club [[AC Milan]] on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite news |title=OFFICIAL STATEMENT: KONI DE WINTER|url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/media/2025-08-13/official-statement-koni-de-winter|date=13 August 2025|access-date=13 August 2025|publisher=AC Milan}}</ref>
On 25 January 2026 he scored his first goal for the club in an away 1-1 draw against Roma.

==International career==
On 23 March 2024, De Winter debuted for the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]] in a [[Exhibition game|friendly match]] against the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Edouard|last=Maréchal|title=Le bizutage de Koni De Winter après sa première avec les Diables Rouges|trans-title=Koni De Winter's haze after his debut with the Red Devils|url=https://www.walfoot.be/news/2024-03-25/--le-bizutage-de-koni-de-winter-apres-sa-premiere-avec-les-diables-rouges|website=Walfoot|date=25 March 2024|access-date=29 August 2024|language=fr}}</ref>

== Positions of play ==
During his career, De Winter has played as a [[central defender]], a [[full-back (association football)|full-back]] on both sides, a [[Defensive Midfielder|defensive midfielder]], and as a [[mezzala]] (specialized midfielder in Italian football).<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|last=Conterio|first=Marco|date=2021-09-10|title=Il primo belga della storia della Juventus: De Winter coi big, l'annuncio arriva da Allegri|url=https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/il-primo-belga-della-storia-della-juventus-de-winter-coi-big-l-annuncio-arriva-da-allegri-1581840|access-date=2021-09-11|website=TUTTOmercatoWEB.com|language=it}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
De Winter was born in Belgium to a Belgian father and Congolese-French mother. De Winter holds both Congolese and French citizenship.<ref name="nieuwsblad.be"/>

